channel.title: Compiler warnings
channel.description:
I know this isn't necessarily needed. But I just am pondering it. I get a bunch of warnings that go something like this: [code].\rsDrawingArea.class: major version 51 is newer then 50, the highest version supported by this compiler. It is recommended that the compiler be upgraded. 29 warnings.[/code]
that just means my JDK is out dated right (though I'm running jdk 6_31 lol)
Can you believe a 317 PI client needs fricking JDK 7_02 to compile and work?
